SIMPLE: lukewarm
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lukewarm
<hw>Luke"warm`</hw> <pr>(l⟦umac⟧k"w⟦add⟧rm`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Luke</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moderately warm;
neither cold nor hot; tepid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not ardent; not zealous; cool; indifferent.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Lukewarm</xex> blood.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Spenser.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧
<xex>Lukewarm</xex> patriots.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An obedience so <qex>lukewarm</qex> and languishing that it merits
not the name of passion.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Luke"warm`ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Luke"warm`ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lull</ent>⟦br⟧
